|| Tomake (\u09a4\u09cb\u09ae\u09be\u0995\u09c7) (Female) || [[Shreya Ghoshal]] \n|\n|-\n|Shei Tumi (\u09b8\u09c7\u0987 \u09a4\u09c1\u09ae\u09bf) ||Arko  \n|\n|-\n|Tomake (\u09a4\u09cb\u09ae\u09be\u0995\u09c7) (Male) ||Arko  \n|\n|}\n\n===Telugu filmography===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| \n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"\n|'''Year'''\n|'''Film Name'''\n|'''Song'''\n|'''Singer(s)'''\n|'''Notes''' \n|-\n|2018 || ''[[Lover (2018 film)|Lover]]'' || What A Ammayi || [[Sonu Nigam]] \n|\n|}\n\n===Album(s)===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| \n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"\n|'''Year(s)'''\n|'''Alum Name(s)'''\n|'''Song(s)'''\n|'''Co-Singer(s)'''\n|'''Composer(s)''' \n|'''Language(s)''' \n|-\n|2015 || ''Mainu Ishq Da Lagya Rog'' || \"Mainu Ishq Da Lagya Rog\" single || [[Tulsi Kumar]] || Original: [[Bhushan Dua]], [[Nadeem-Shravan]], Recreated by: Arko || Hindi\n|-\n|2018 || ''Bepanah'' || \"Bepanah\" || [[Tina Kundalia]], Arko || [[Rishabh Shrivastava]] || Hindi\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2019 || rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Oriplast Originals]]'' || \"Baundule (\u09ac\u09be\u0989\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09c1\u09b2\u09c7)\" || [[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]], Arko || rowspan=\"3\"|Arko || rowspan=\"2\"|Bengali\n|-\n|\"Bola Jaye Na (\u09ac\u09b2\u09be \u09af\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u09a8\u09be)\" || [[Akriti Kakar]], Arko \n|-\n|''[[Akhbaar]]'' || \"Akhbaar\" || Arko || Hindi\n|}\n\n==Film songs==\nIn 2012, Arko debuted as a music composer in ''[[Jism 2]]''. He composed four songs for it. In 2014, he composed two songs for ''[[Yaariyan (2014 film)|Yaariyan]]'' for which he earned a nomination of [[Filmfare Award for Best Music Director]] along with [[Pritam]], [[Mithoon]], [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]] and [[Anupam Amod]]. In the same year, he composed songs for ''[[Hate Story 2]]'', ''[[Tamanchey]]'' and ''[[The Shaukeens]]''. In 2015, he composed for ''[[Kuch Kuch Locha Hai]]'', ''[[Bhaag Johnny]]'', ''[[Jazbaa]]''. In 2016, he composed a song for ''[[Kapoor & Sons]]'' and ''[[Baar Baar Dekho]]''. He also composed two songs for ''[[Rustom (film)|Rustom]]''. He earned another nomination of [[Filmfare Award for Best Music Director]] for ''Kapoor & Sons along with [[Amaal Mallik]], [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]], [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Benny Dayal]] & [[Nucleya]]. In 2017, he composed for ''[[Sweetiee Weds NRI]]'', ''[[Dobaara: See Your Evil]]'', ''[[Laali Ki Shaadi Mein Laaddoo Deewana]]'', ''[[Bareilly Ki Barfi]]'' and a single titled 'Aainda'. He received his third nomination of [[Filmfare Award for Best Music Director]] for ''Bareilly Ki Barfi'' along with [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Samira Koppikar]], [[Vayu]] and [[Sameer Uddin]]. He also earned a nomination of [[Filmfare Award for Best Lyrics]] for the same film. In 2018, Arko composed a song for ''[[Hate Story 4]]'' and a song for ''[[Baaghi 2]]''. He composes for ''[[Gold (2018 film)|Gold]]'' and ''[[Satyamev Jayate (2018 film)|Satyamev Jayate]]''.\n\nArko Pravo Mukherjee rendered his voice as the playback singer for the first time in \"Saathi Re\" for ''[[Kapoor & Sons]]''<ref>{{cite news |date=9 April 2016 |title= It's not always been my call: Composer Arko Pravo Mukherjee on turning singer only now |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-it-s-not-always-been-my-call-composer-arko-pravo-mukherjee-on-turning-singer-only-now-2200007 |work=Daily News and Analysis}}</ref> following ''[[Rustom (film)|Rustom]]'', ''[[Baar Baar Dekho]]'', ''[[Laali Ki Shaadi Mein Laaddoo Deewana]]'', ''[[Tum Bin II]]'', ''[[Sweetiee Weds NRI]]'', ''[[Dobaara: See Your Evil]]'', ''[[Bareilly Ki Barfi]]'', ''[[Daas Dev]]'' and a single titled \"Aainda\". He is the main singer of \"Jogi\" in the film ''[[Shaadi Mein Zaroor Aana]]''.\n\n==Non-film songs==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| \n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- \n! style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"|'''Year(s)'''\n! style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"|'''Song(s)'''\n! style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"|'''Singer(s)'''\n! style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"|'''Language(s)'''\n|-\n|| 2020  || SUNO NA || Arko & Neeti Mohan \n|-\n|| 2020 || Tum Jo Mil Gaye || Ash king & [[Lisa Mishra]]\n|-\n|| 2019  || Baashinda || Arko & Ankit Tiwari & Ragini Tandon || rowspan=\"6\" |Hindi\n|- \n|| 2019 || Dard E Dil || Ankit Tiwari & Priyanka Negi\n|- \n|| 2019 || Ek Pyaar Ka Nagma || Papon Neeti Mohan \n|- \n||2019  || Baarishein || [[Atif Aslam]]\n|-\n||2019  || Akhbaar  || [[Arko Pravo Mukherjee]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2017 || Aainda<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/music/riteish-deshmukh-makes-debut-in-pop-world-with-arko-pravo-mukherjee-song-aainda-see-photos-4790471/|title=Riteish Deshmukh makes debut in pop world with Arko Pravo Mukherjee's song Aainda. See photos|date=10 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/english/music/news/madalina-ghenea-to-feature-in-arko-pravo-mukherjis-pop-song-aainda/articleshow/59953890.cms|title=Madalina Bellariu to feature in Arko Pravo Mukherji's pop song 'AAINDA' \u2013 Times of India}}</ref> ||Arko Pravo Mukherjee \n|-\n|| Salaam-e-Ishq<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mediainfoline.com/music/launch-single-salaam-e-ishq-actor-shilpi-sharma-arko|title=Launch of single Salaam-E-Ishq by Dj & Actor Shilpi Sharma and Arko \u2013 Media Infoline|date=20 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saregama.com/video/salaameishq-arko-dj-shilpi-sharma-i-jasmine-sandlas_294|title=Salaam-e-Ishq \u2013 Arko & DJ Shilpi Sharma I Jasmine Sandlas \u2013 listen and download music videos from Saregama}}</ref> || Producer/Remixer \u2013 DJ [[Shilpi Sharma]],<br/>Male vocalist -Arko Pravo Mukherjee<br/>Female vocalist \u2013 [[Jasmine]]\n|-\n|| Reeva<ref>{{cite news |date=3 April 2017 |title= Arko's New Song 'Reeva' Features on Billboard Dance Club Chart |url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/arkos-new-song-reeva-features-on-billboard-dance-club-chart-1367541.html |work=news18.com}}</ref> || Arko Pravo Mukherjee \n|-\n| 2015|| Mainu Ishq Da Lagya Rog<ref>{{cite news |date=10 October 2015 |title= Tulsi Kumar-Arko Pravo Mukherjee collaborate for Khushali Kumar's next |url=http://www.indiablooms.com/ibns_new/showbiz-details/B/2658/tulsi-kumar-arko-pravo-mukherjee-collaborate-for-khushali-kumar-s-next.html |work=India Blooms}}</ref> || [[Tulsi Kumar]]  ||\n|-\n| 2013 || Maa<ref>{{cite news |date=12 May 2013|title= A Melodious Mother's Day Tribute From Arko Pravo Mukherjee |url=http://www.koimoi.com/bollywood-news/a-melodious-mothers-day-tribute-from-arko-pravo-mukherjee/ |work=koimoi}}</ref> || Arko Pravo Mukherjee|| Bengali\n|-\n| 2011 || Mira (Hindi album)<ref>{{cite news |date=25 September 2011|title= The songwriter duo Arko & Dev is a UFO in the sky of Indipop |url=http://www.artisttrove.com/artist/165853623478005/Arko+%26+Dev |work=Artist Trove}}</ref> || Arko Pravo Mukherjee & Dev(Bishwadeb Bhaumik) || Hindi\n|-\n|}\n\nArko Pravo Mukherjee is planning to record an English album in Los Angeles soon.<ref>{{cite news |date=13 March 2016|title= Arko Pravo Mukherjee keen to record English album |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/music/arko-pravo-mukherjee-keen-to-record-english-album/ |work=The Indian Express}}</ref>\nHis song 'Reeva' has become the No.1 Break Out Song for the Billboard Dance Club 50 Charts.As per the 1 April reports, the track entered the Billboard Dance 50 Charts at Number 49.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/error404.cms|title=Most Viewed Business News Articles, Top News Articles|website=The Economic Times}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n'''Nominations'''\n* Best Debut Music 2012 \u2013 [[Stardust Awards|Stardust]] ([[Jism 2]])\n* Best Debut Lyrics 2012 \u2013 [[Stardust Awards|Stardust]] ([[Jism 2]])\n* Best Sufi song 2012 \u2013 [[Global Indian Music Academy Awards|GIMA]] \n* Best debut Music Director 2013 \u2013 [[Global Indian Music Academy Awards|GIMA]] \n* Best Lyrics 2013 \u2013 [[Global Indian Music Academy Awards|GIMA]]\n* Best Music 2014 for Yaariyan \u2013 nominated at [[Filmfare Awards]], [[International Indian Film Academy Awards|IIFA awards]], [[Screen Awards]] etc.\n* Awarded Gold Disc \u2013 Mirchi Top 20 \nAaj Phir Tum Pe \u2013 Hate Story 2\n* Nominated Best Singer Debut \u2013 Saathi Re ( Kapoor & Son's )\n* Nominated Filmfare Best Music Director- Saathi Re ( Kapoor & Son's )\n* Awarded TIFFA \u2013 Best Music Director ( Song Of the Year \u2013 Tere Sang yaara )\n* Awarded Platinum Disc \u2013 Mirchi Top 20 ( Tere Sang Yaara )\n\n\n'''Awards'''\n* Won STAR SCREEN Awards as Best Music Composer for movie ''Yaariyan'' alongside Pritam, Mithoon, Yo Yo Honey Singh\n\n==Notable achievements==\n* Arko was featured on The Billboard Charts List. Arko's Latest English single \"Reeva\" was the 45th song on the Billboard Dance Club top 50 Charts.<ref>{{cite news |date=10 April 2017|title= Arko Is The First Indian on the Billboard Charts List! |url=https://www.festivalsherpa.com/icymi-arko-first-indian-billboard-charts-list/ |work=festivalsherpa.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/indian-singer-arko-features-on-billboard-charts-117040300040_1.html|title=Indian singer Arko features on Billboard Charts |agency=IANS |date=3 April 2017 |newspaper=Business Standard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/arko-singer-billboard-dance-50-charts-reeva-rustom-jism-2-lifest/1/947845.html|title=Here's why singer Arko is the man on the Billboard|website=India Today}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/entertainment/editorial/news/170403-indian-singer-arko-features-on-billboard|title=Indian singer Arko features on Billboard Charts}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://toplyricssite.com/tag/arko//|title= Indian Singer Arko Top Song List- TopLyricsSite|website=TiplyricsSite|language=English|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n* Awarded as the Prominent Bengali of the year 2016 \u2013 Awarded by [[Indian Oil Corporation]] and the tabloid ''[[Ebela]]'' (ABP Group)\n* Best Music Director Award for the song 'Tere Sang Yaara' from the film [[Rustom (film)|Rustom]] (Zee [[ETC Bollywood Business Awards]] 2016)\n* Singers who have made their debut for Arko in Bollywood include Samira Koppikar, Jubin Nautiyal, Nilofer Wani, Neha Pandey, [[Yasser Desai (Singer)|Yasser Desai]] and B-Praak\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=5120317}}\n* {{Facebook|ARKOWORLD|Arko Pravo Mukherjee}}\n* {{Twitter|ArkoPravo19|Arko Pravo Mukherjee}}\n* [http://www.arkoworld.com Official Website]\n* [https://www.bollywoodlyrica.com/2019/11/aaina-lyrics-body-main-rahu-tere-samane.html Arko Latest Song]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mukherjee, Arko Pravo}}\n[[Category:Music directors]]\n[[Category:Bengali people]]\n[[Category:Bengali Hindus]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Kolkata]]\n[[Category:Indian film score composers]]\n[[Category:Indian guitarists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Hindi film score composers]]\n[[Category:21st-century guitarists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian singer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                 = Arko Pravo Mukherjee\n| image                = Arko2.jpg\n| caption              = Arko Pravo Mukherjee\n| birth_name           = Arko Pravo Mukherjee\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1983|005|19}}\n| birth_place          = [[Kolkata]], West Bengal, India\n| yearsactive          = 2012\u2013present\n| occupation           = {{hlist|Music composer|singer-songwriter}}\n| genre                = Bengali modern\n| website              = http://www.arkoworld.com/\n| background           = solo_singer\n}}\nDr. Arko Pravo Mukherjee is an Indian [[singer-songwriter]] working in the Bollywood film industry since 2012. ''[[Jism 2]]'' was his debut film as a music composer and lyricist.<ref>{{cite news |date=1 August 2012 |title= 'Jism 2' songs are not copied, says composer |url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/india/jism-2-songs-are-not-copied-says-composer-493266.html |work=IBN Live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=17 April 2012 |title= Arko to compose music for 'Jism 2' |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/music/news-and-interviews/Arko-to-compose-music-for-Jism-2/articleshow/12700322.cms?referral=PM |work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=28 April 2012 |title= New Prescription Arko Pravo Mukherjee to compose music for Jism 2 |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/arko-pravo-mukherjee-to-compose-music-for-jism-2/1/186437.html |work=India Today}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=1 December 2014 |title= A quick four with Arko Pravo Mukherjee |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141201/entertainment-tvmusic/article/quick-four-arko-pravo-mukherjee |work=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=7 November 2014 |title= Arko Pravo Mukherjee sings an EDM number |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/screen/arko-pravo-mukherjee-sings-an-edm-number/ |work=The Indian Express}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=10 February 2015 |title= Tips Music signs Arko Pravo Mukherjee for ten songs of their upcoming films |url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/biz/music/artiste/tips-music-signs-arko-pravo-mukherjee-ten-songs-their-upcoming-films-150210 |work=Radio And Music}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=13 February 2015 |title= On a high note: Arko Pravo Mukherjee |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/screen/on-a-high-note-arko-pravo-mukherjee/ |work=The Indian Express}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=8 August 2012 |title= Item songs don't work anymore: Dr Arko Pravo Mukherjee |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Item-songs-dont-work-anymore-Dr-Arko-Pravo-Mukherjee/articleshow/15400604.cms |work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=7 February 2015 |title=Signing A Deal |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.co.in/signing-a-deal/ |publisher=Box Office India |access-date=12 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222074025/http://www.boxofficeindia.co.in/signing-a-deal/ |archive-date=22 December 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=28 November 2014 |title= Nothing works beyond Bollywood, says 'Aaj Phir Tum Pe' singer Arko |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/music/nothing-works-beyond-bollywood-says-aaj-phir-tum-pe-singer-arko/story-oT7jLq630CZqKAWDG8AELI.html |work=Hindustan Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=29 December 2014 |title= 2014 Rewind: Bollywood musicians pick their favourite songs of the year |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/2014-rewind-bollywood-musicians-pick-their-favourite-songs-of-the-year/15873179 |work=MidDay}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=14 July 2012 |title= Music Review: 'Jism 2' has wonderful tracks |url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/music/music-review-jism-2-has-wonderful-tracks-487734.html |work=IBN Live}}</ref>He is also known for singing several Bengali and Nepali music. According to Industry Experts and Bollywood Media Reviews, Arko is among the most promising new sensations in Indian Music and is also among the busiest Music Directors of Bollywood.<ref>https://m.imdb.com/name/nm3334275/bio?ref_=m_mn_ov_bio</ref><ref>https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/bengali/music/arko-pravo-mukherjee-is-a-married-man/amp_articleshow/66360261.cmsp</ref><ref>https://m.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/kriti-sanons-bareilly-ki-barfi-movie-songs.html</ref><ref>https://scroll.in/reel/804588/composer-arko-mukherjee-raises-the-pitch-with-kapoor-sons</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nArko Pravo Mukherjee was born on 19 May 1983 to Dr. Apurba Kumar Mukherjee and Mahasweta Mukherjee in [[Kolkata]], West Bengal. He attended school at [[Don Bosco School, Park Circus]], Kolkata. Arko graduated with MBBS in 2007 from [[Burdwan Medical College]]. He completed his internship at [[Calcutta Medical College]] and then in 2008 he shifted to Mumbai to pursue a career in Bollywood film industry as a music director, singer songwriter.<ref>{{cite news |date=4 October 2015 |title= MEET DR DO MORE OF MUSIC |url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/sunday-edition/sunday-pioneer/backpack/meet-dr-do-more-of-music.html |work=Daily Pioneer}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=9 December 2014 |title=Rising Arko Pravo sets solid foot in Bollywood |url=http://archive.asianage.com/people/rising-arko-pravo-sets-solid-foot-bollywood-547 |work=The Asian Age |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222170522/http://archive.asianage.com/people/rising-arko-pravo-sets-solid-foot-bollywood-547 |archivedate=22 December 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=2 December 2014 |title=A quick four with Arko Pravo |url=http://archive.asianage.com/music/quick-four-arko-pravo-147 |work=The Asian Age |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222170445/http://archive.asianage.com/music/quick-four-arko-pravo-147 |archivedate=22 December 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=2 November 2015 |title= Melody matters |url=http://www.asianage.com/music/melody-matters-504 |work=The Asian Age}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Hindi filmography===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| \n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"\n|'''Year'''\n|'''Film Name/Album'''\n|'''Song'''\n|'''Singer(s)'''\n|'''Notes''' \n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2012 ||rowspan=4|''[[Jism 2]]''<ref>{{cite news |date=14 July 2012 |title= Made in Calcutta: A DBPC boy has scored the soundtrack. Meet Arko Pravo Mukherjee |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120714/jsp/entertainment/story_15725199.jsp |work=The Telegraph}}</ref>  || Abhi Abhi (Male) || [[KK (singer)|KK]] ||\n|-\n|| Yeh Jism Hai Toh Kya<ref>{{cite news |date=3 August 2012 |title= \"Yeh Jism' is very close to my heart\" \u2013 Dr.Arko Pravo Mukherjee |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/3778/ |work=Bollywood Hungama}}</ref> ||rowspan=\"2\"|[[Ali Azmat]]\n|\n|-\n|| Maula\n|\n|-\n|| Abhi Abhi (Duet) || KK, [[Akriti Kakar]], [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|2014 || rowspan=2|''[[Yaariyan (2014 film)|Yaariyan]]''<ref>{{cite news |date=27 December 2013 |title= I don't mind being part of a multi- composer movie: Arko Pravo Mukherjee |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Arko-Pravo-Mukherjee-takes-us-through-his-eventful-journey-in-Bollywood/articleshow/27976957.cms? |work=The Times of India}}</ref> || Allah Waariyan || [[Shafqat Amanat Ali]] \n|\n|-\n|| Zor Lagaake Haisha || [[Vishal Dadlani]] \n|\n|-\n|| ''[[Hate Story 2]]'' || Aaj Phir Tumpe Pyaar Aaya Hai || [[Arijit Singh]], [[Samira Koppikar]]\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Tamanchey]]'' || Dildara || [[Sonu Nigam]] ||\n|-\n||Dildara (Reprise) || Arko\n|\n|-\n|| ''[[The Shaukeens]]''<ref>{{cite news |date=23 October 2014 |title= The Shaukeens : On a Song \u2013 What started in the studio ended at a party |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/The-Shaukeens-On-a-Song-What-started-in-the-studio-ended-at-a-party/articleshow/44915285.cms |work=The Times of India}}</ref> || Meherbani<ref>{{cite news |date=5 November 2014 |title= Arko Pravo Mukherjee: 'Meherbani' was completed in a couple of days |url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/entertainment/editorial/news/arko-pravo-mukherjee-meherbani-was-completed-couple-days |work=Radio And Music}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=23 October 2014 |title= WHAT STARTED IN THE STUDIO ENDED AT A PARTY |url=http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertain